## Shipping Method [/v1/orders/{refNum}/shipping-methods]

Shipping methods are used to describe the ways that the contents of a cart can
transported to the customer. All actions that occur against this set of
endpoints modify which shipping method is used by the cart.

### List [GET]

Returns the list of all shipping methods that may be applied to this cart.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (ShippingMethod)

### Update [PATCH]

Changes the shipping method to a cart.

+ Parameters
    + refNum: 1 (required, string) - Order referenceNumber
+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (CreateShippingAddressPayload)
+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (FullOrder)

### Delete [DELETE]

Removes the shipping method from the cart.

+ Parameters
    + refNum: 1 (required, string) - Order reference number
+ Response 204
